        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"515757\">Luke Boswell</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/395097-compiler-development/topic/casual.20conversation/near/492411962\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I wonder if we could just commit the html files into the repo under a folder structure... </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>www/\n- 0.16.0/\n- 0.17.0/\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I'm not sure if this is compatible with GH pages...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I've been messing around with this... it'd be really nice if we had a flag in roc cli <code>roc docs --mount \"/0.11.0/\"</code> that could say, hey generate the static site but assume you will be mounted at this folder <code>/0.11.0/</code> or something... so all the links point at the correct location and there is no need to replace things.</p>",
        "id": 492417224,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1736298905
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/casual.20conversation/near/492417224\">A message</a> was moved here from <a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"395097\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/395097-compiler-development/topic/casual.20conversation\">#compiler development &gt; casual conversation</a> by <span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"515757\">Luke Boswell</span>.</p>",
